thlib/Logic/Function/Defs.html#Function.Bijective\">Function.Bijective</a> <span class=\"fn\">⇑<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/LocalRing/ResidueField/Ideal.html#Ideal.ResidueField.mapₐ\">Ideal.ResidueField.mapₐ</a> <span class=\"fn\">p</span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Hom.html#Algebra.ofId\">ofId</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">R'</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">⋯</span>)</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>         <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Finiteness/Defs.html#Module.Finite\">Module.Finite</a> <span class=\"fn\">R'</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/GroupTheory/MonoidLocalization/Away.html#Localization.Away\">Localization.Away</a> <span class=\"fn\">e</span>)</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#And\">∧</a>           <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">P''</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Defs.html#Ideal\">Ideal</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/TensorProduct/Defs.html#TensorProduct\">TensorProduct</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span> <span class=\"fn\">R'</span> <span class=\"fn\">S</span>)</span></span>), <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P''</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Prime.html#Ideal.IsPrime\">IsPrime</a></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">P''</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Ideal/Over.html#Ideal.LiesOver\">LiesOver</a></span> <span class=\"fn\">P</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">e</span> ∉ <span class=\"fn\">P''</span></span> → <span class=\"fn\">P''</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">P'</span></span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `S` be a finite type `R`-algebra, and `q` a prime lying over `p` such that `S` is quasi-finite\nat `q`.\nWe may construct an etale `R`-algebra `R'` and a prime `P` lying over `p` with `κ(P) = κ(p)`,\nsuch that `R' ⊗[R] S = A × B`, `A` is finite as an `R'`-module,\nand there exists a unique prime in `A` lying over `P`. This prime will also lie over `q`.\n\nThe actual lemma is stated in terms of the idempotent element `e = (1, 0)`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Etale/QuasiFinite.html#Algebra.exists_etale_isIdempotentElem_forall_liesOver_eq","kind":"theorem","line":372,"name":"Algebra.exists_etale_isIdempotentElem_forall_liesOver_eq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/RingTheory/Etale/QuasiFinite.lean#L372-L441"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Etale/QuasiFinite.html#Algebra.exists_etale_isIdempotentElem_forall_liesOver_eq_aux₂\"><span class=\"name\">Algebra</span>.<span class=\"name\">exists_etale_isIdempotentElem_forall_liesOver_eq_aux₂</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">S</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R'</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">R''</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_5}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommRing\">CommRing</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span 